news.title: Homesfy Realty raises $1.1 million ahead of planned SME IPO
news.para: The proceeds from the proposed offering will be used by the company for its working capital requirements, general corporate purpose, and organic growth.

news.title: Facade lighting to be soon mandatory for highrise buildings in Greater Noida
news.para: In the first phase, lights will be installed on buildings along both sides of the 105m wide road in front of the Greater Noida authority’s office and a 130m wide stretch connecting Greater Noida with Noida Extension.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body scouts for land, will sell it to raise funds for metro projects
news.para: In fact, the GDA has directed its land department to identify plots it has failed to acquire to date, officials said. The authority hopes to fund the over Rs 3,000-crore ambitious metro projects by selling off these plots.

news.title: Gurugram: Builder fails to pay dues, power to Raheja Mall snapped, traders protest
news.para: The protesters alleged that the developer has collected maintenance and electricity charges from them but didn’t deposit the money with the discom, leading to disconnection of power supply.

news.title: Signature Global gets Sebi nod for its Rs 1,000 crore proposed IPO
news.para: As per the DRHP, the IPO will comprise a fresh issue of equity shares worth up to Rs 750 crore and an Offer for Sale (OFS) of up to Rs 250 crore. Promoter Sarvpriya Securities and investor International Finance Corporation will sell equity shares worth up to Rs 125 crore each.

news.title: NBCC gets Rs 271.62 crore order in stalled projects of erstwhile Amrapali Group
news.para: ​In a regulatory filing, the company informed that it has got an order of Rs 42.44 crore for construction of balance works /left out works of Amrapali corporate Hub at IMT Manesar, Gurugram in Haryana.

news.title: China Evergrande aims to win approval for restructuring proposals early next year
news.para: Once China's top-selling developer, Evergrande is now at the centre of the country's property crisis. Its $22.7 billion of offshore debt, including loans and private bonds, is deemed to be in default after missed payments late last year.

news.title: Road, metro projects to link Jewar airport on the anvil
news.para: A high-speed rail link has been proposed at one of the terminals that will connect to Delhi in just 21 minutes. The Metro line from Greater Noida will also be extended to Noida and the north and east areas of the airport will be linked with roads.

news.title: Supreme court says Andhra HC cannot be 'town planner'
news.para: It observed the Andhra Pradesh High Court cannot be a "town planner" or an "engineer" and direct the government that the capital city should come up in six months.

news.title: Airport Express Metro on track, Telangana CM to lay foundation on Dec 9
news.para: The idea for the Airport Express Metro Corridor, part of Phase 2 of Metro project, was first floated in 2019. The Hyderabad Airport Metro Rail (HAML) shared that the corridor will have 27 km of elevated and 1 km on ground network.

news.title: Shapoorji Pallonji Real Estate raises Rs 450 crore from Motilal Oswal for two projects
news.para: One of the projects is a partially completed, leased and operational commercial project located in Manesar. The other project is a residential township project, launched in 2021 and has seen a positive sales response.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government notifies 804.5 sq km in Trichy as urban planning area
news.para: Once the notification is published in the government and district gazette, the department will constitute a board for the authority to create a detailed development plan for better utilisation of the land parcels in the urban planning area.

news.title: Nashik civic body to create green buffer zone around proposed construction waste plant
news.para: Nashik civic body will also plant more than 3,000 saplings on around 70 acre of the area proposed for the C&D waste plant, which is to be built at the cost of Rs7 crore soon.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body mulls special squad to curb construction plan violations
news.para: The officials are finding deviations from the approved online plan during the construction phase in several instances. This could be due to some people uploading doctored documents to meet the requirements and get online approvals.

news.title: Property survey in Secunderabad Cantonment moves at snail's pace
news.para: This census survey is aimed at enumerating every property in the Cantonment based on the inputs received from the drone survey, taken up under the Survey of Villages and Mapping with Improvised Technology in Village Areas (Svamitva) scheme.
